# chord `spread` separating doubled notes into octaves. Two notes (select1/3 =
# C,E) in 4-voice mode duplicate to C,E,C,E. spread=1V (0.1) makes the allowed
# lowest->highest span 2 octaves (12 + 12 = 24 semitones), so the doubled C and E
# move up an octave instead of collapsing to unisons.
# SPEC-GAP: only octave-separation of doubled voices is modelled here; the
# manual's "distribute the remaining notes with the most equal spacing possible"
# across a >1-octave spread is NOT modelled (needs hardware reference). Non-
# doubled voices stay in the base octave.
#   O1=C(0), O2=E(4), O3=C+oct(12), O4=E+oct(16)
patch <<<
[chord]
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    output3 = O3
    output4 = O4
    select1 = 1
    select3 = 1
    spread  = 1V
>>>
@0 expect O1 0 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O2 0.0333333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O3 0.1 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O4 0.1333333 tol 1e-5
